A Finnish frequency list from Finnish printed news[edit]

The 9996 most common lemmas of the language of Finnish printed news (Under Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivs-NonCommercial 1.0 Finland (CC BY-ND-NC 1.0)). The vocabulary was assembled in 2004 and the total count of the source material was 43,999,826 words.

if percentage = count / (count of the source material 43,999,826) *100 , the data in columns count or percentage are not correct  !!! But if we suppose that count of the source material was 58,862,077 words - not 43,999,826, data in columns count and percentage are relevant with formula percentage = count / (count of the source material) *100
